# Scene Rendering System Documentation

## Overview

The Hexagotchi rendering system is built around a modular scene architecture where each scene manages its own actors, effects, and rendering logic. The system uses Raylib for 2D rendering with a camera system, layer-based actor sorting, and scene transition effects.

The game uses a **gotchi mode / story mode** core loop:
- **Gotchi Mode**: Pet simulation with buttons (feed, pet, wash, merge) on `GotchiScene`
- **Story Mode**: Narrative scenes (Pizza Parlor, Apartment, Office, etc.) accessed via merge transition
- **Transitions**: `MergeScene` provides the literal door-through transition between modes

---

## Architecture Diagram

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                             Game Rendering Pipeline                          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                              │
│  1. UpdateDrawFrame() [main.cpp]                                            │
│     ├─ SyncMouseToGameSpace()  ← Mouse coordinate correction                │
│     ├─ sceneManager->update(dt)                                             │
│     ├─ dialog->update(dt)                                                   │
│     ├─ mergeController->update(dt)                                          │
│     ├─ storySequencer->update(dt)                                           │
│     └─ BeginTextureMode(gameTarget)                                         │
│           ├─ sceneManager->draw()                                           │
│           ├─ dialog->draw()                                                 │
│           └─ EndTextureMode()                                               │
│                                                                              │
│  2. Letterbox Scaling (main.cpp)                                            │
│     └─ DrawTexturePro(gameTarget, srcRect, destRect, rotation, WHITE)      │
│                                                                              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Scene System

### Scene Base Class (`src/engine/Scene.hpp/.cpp`)

All scenes inherit from the `Scene` base class which provides:

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Lifecycle** | `init()`, `update(deltaTime)`, `draw()`, `cleanup()` |
| **Actor Management** | `addActor()`, `removeActor()`, `findActorByTag()` |
| **Camera** | `getCamera()`, `createCamera()` |
| **Effects** | `addEffect()` for background/foreground visual effects |
| **Input** | `getInputHandler()` for keyboard/mouse input |
| **State** | `setPaused()`, `togglePause()` |
| **Story Events** | `triggerStoryEvent()` for narrative scenes |

### Scene Constants

```cpp
const Color SCENE_DEFAULT_BG = RAYWHITE;        // Default background color
const float SCENE_DEFAULT_WIDTH = 1920.0f;      // Default scene width
const float SCENE_DEFAULT_HEIGHT = 1080.0f;     // Default scene height
```

### Scene Size by Type

| Scene Type | Width | Height | Background |
|------------|-------|--------|------------|
| Gotchi/Pet Scenes | 720 | 720 | Dark purple |
| Narrative Scenes | 720 | 720 | Varies by scene |
| Title/Menu Scenes | 720 | 720 | Black |
| Debug/Test Scenes | 720 | 720 | Varies |

