## Rendering Pipeline

### Main Loop (`UpdateDrawFrame()` in main.cpp)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   UpdateDrawFrame() - Main Game Loop                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                         │
│  1. Sync Mouse Coordinates                                                │
│     ├─ GetLetterboxRect() - Calculate scaled drawing area               │
│     └─ SetMouseOffset/SetMouseScale() - Adjust for letterboxing         │
│                                                                         │
│  2. Scene Management                                                      │
│     ├─ Check scene transitions and update dialogIndex                   │
│     ├─ Handle scene-specific dialog display rules                       │
│     └─ Process input triggers for scene switching                       │
│                                                                         │
│  3. Update Phase                                                          │
│     ├─ sceneManager->update(dt) - Update current scene                  │
│     ├─ dialog->update(dt) - Update dialog box state                     │
│     ├─ mergeController->update(dt) - Merge availability logic           │
│     ├─ storySequencer->update(dt) - Story beat progression              │
│     ├─ gotchiSim->update(dt) - Gotchi simulation reducer                │
│     └─ driversController->update(dt) - Affection/Mercy computation      │
│                                                                         │
│  4. Render to Offscreen Texture (gameTarget)                             │
│     ├─ ClearBackground(BLACK)                                           │
│     ├─ sceneManager->draw() - Render scene                              │
│     ├─ dialog->draw() - Render dialog overlay                           │
│     └─ Draw scene-specific overlay labels (top-left corner)             │
│                                                                         │
│  5. Letterbox Scaling to Window                                          │
│     ├─ GetLetterboxRect() - Calculate destination rectangle             │
│     └─ DrawTexturePro() - Draw gameTarget to window with scaling        │
│                                                                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Scene Drawing Order (`Scene::draw()`)

```cpp
void Scene::draw() {
    // 1. Clear background
    ClearBackground(backgroundColor);

    // 2. Draw background effects (rendered first, behind actors)
    for (auto effect : effects) {
        effect->drawBackground();
        rlDisableDepthTest();
    }

    // 3. Draw actors in 2D camera mode (sorted by layer)
    if (camera) BeginMode2D(camera->getRaylibCamera());
    for (auto actor : actors) {
        if (actor->isVisible()) actor->draw();
    }
    if (camera) EndMode2D();

    // 4. Draw foreground effects (rendered last, on top of actors)
    for (auto effect : effects) {
        effect->drawForeground();
        rlDisableDepthTest();
    }
}
```

### Actor Layer System

```cpp
const int ACTOR_LAYER_BACKGROUND = 0;   // Farthest back
const int ACTOR_LAYER_MIDGROUND = 1;    // Mid layer
const int ACTOR_LAYER_FOREGROUND = 2;   // In front
const int ACTOR_LAYER_UI = 3;           // Topmost (UI elements)
```

Actors are automatically sorted by layer during `addActor()` and `processRemovals()`.

---

## SceneActor System

### SceneActor Base Class (`src/engine/SceneActor.hpp/.cpp`)

The base class for all renderable entities provides:

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Transform** | Position, rotation, scale, velocity |
| **Physics** | Friction, gravity, collision detection |
| **Animation** | Sprite sheets and frame lists |
| **Clickability** | Hover/press states with callbacks |
| **Layers** | Z-order control via layer property |
| **Tags** | String-based identification |

### SceneActor Constants

```cpp
const float ACTOR_DEFAULT_FRICTION = 0.98f;
const float ACTOR_GRAVITY = 300.0f;
const Color ACTOR_HOVER_TINT = {255, 255, 255, 60};   // 25% white on hover
const Color ACTOR_PRESSED_TINT = {0, 0, 0, 70};        // ~27% black on press
```

### SceneActor Rendering

Each actor's `draw()` method is responsible for rendering itself. Common patterns:

#### Simple Rectangle Drawing
```cpp
void draw() override {
    DrawRectangle((int)position.x, (int)position.y, (int)width, (int)height, color);
}
```

#### Sprite with Animation
```cpp
// In init():
actor->setAnimation(frameWidth, frameHeight, frameCount, frameDuration, loop);

// draw() uses texture automatically when animation is set
```

#### Custom Shape Drawing
```cpp
void draw() override {
    Vector2 p = getPosition();
    DrawCircle((int)p.x, (int)p.y, radius, color);
    DrawCircleLines((int)p.x, (int)p.y, radius + 5, outlineColor);
}
```

---

## Camera System

### SceneCamera Class (`src/engine/SceneCamera.hpp/.cpp`)

Features:

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Position** | Follow actors or positions with smooth lerp |
| **Zoom** | Dynamic zoom with duration-based transitions |
| **Rotation** | Camera rotation with smooth transitions |
| **Lookahead** | Camera looks ahead in direction of movement |
| **Shake** | Screen shake effect with decay |
| **Boundaries** | Clamp camera to world bounds |
| **Wide View** | Toggle to see entire scene at once (for 3D placement) |

### Camera Constants

```cpp
const float CAMERA_DEFAULT_ZOOM = 1.0f;
const float CAMERA_MIN_ZOOM = 0.5f;
const float CAMERA_MAX_ZOOM = 5.0f;
const float CAMERA_FOLLOW_SPEED = 5.0f;
const float CAMERA_SHAKE_DAMPING = 0.95f;
const float CAMERA_LOOKAHEAD_DISTANCE = 100.0f;
```

### Camera Usage Example

```cpp
// Follow player with custom speed
getCamera()->followActor(player, 4.0f);

// Dynamic zoom based on player velocity
float targetZoom = 1.0f - (playerVelocityY / 420.0f) * 0.25f;
getCamera()->zoomTo(targetZoom, 0.1f);

// Screen shake on landing
getCamera()->shake(4.0f, 0.15f);

// Camera boundaries
getCamera()->setBoundary(0, -200, 4800.0f, 900.0f);
```

---

## Effects System

### SceneEffect Base Class (`src/engine/SceneEffect.hpp`)

Effects are rendered outside the 2D camera mode, allowing them to:
- Render in world space (parallax starfield)
- Render in 3D space (moon with lighting)
- Render in screen space (overlays)

### StarfieldEffect (`src/effects/StarfieldEffect.cpp`)

A parallax background effect with two layers:

| Layer | Star Count | Parallax Factor | Rendering |
|-------|-----------|-----------------|-----------|
| Background stars | 200 | 0.1x | Single pixels |
| Mid stars | 80 | 0.25x | Small circles (1.2px radius) |

### MoonEffect (`src/effects/MoonEffect.cpp`)

A 3D-rendered moon with:
- **Shader-based lighting**: Custom GLSL shaders for WebGL and desktop OpenGL
- **Directional light**: Simulates sunlight from a moving source
- **Animated rotation**: The moon slowly rotates
- **Day/Night cycle**: Light position follows sine wave motion

### GrimeShader (`src/effects/GrimeShader.hpp/cpp`)

Applies a grime/dishevelment overlay to the gotchi based on neglect levels.

### PortalShader / PortalEffect (`src/effects/PortalEffect.hpp/cpp`)

The merge transition effect - a ring-shaped portal with 3D geometry. Used in both:
- `MergeScene` for the literal transition
- `OfficeScene` as a background element (pixel-locked to the scene)

---

## Dialog Box System

### DialogBox Class (`src/engine/DialogBox.hpp/.cpp`)

A shared dialogue system used across narrative scenes.

**Key Features**:
- Character reveal animation (typing effect)
- Option selection with keyboard navigation
- Fade in/out transitions
- Portrait display (optional texture or silhouette)
- Text wrapping for multi-line dialogue
- `setOnFinished()` callback for scene progression

**Position**: Anchored at bottom of screen (y = GAME_H - 20)

**Dimensions**: 680px wide × 160px high

### DialogBox Rendering

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     Dialog Box Layout                              │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                    │
│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │  Speaker Name (colored text)                                │   │
│  │  ┌──────┐                                                   │   │
│  │  │Portrait│   Dialogue Text (wraps to fit width)          │   │
│  │  │(120x│   ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐      │   │
│  │  │ 120) │   │This is the main dialogue text that    │      │   │
│  │  │      │   │wraps across multiple lines based on   │      │   │
│  │  │      │   │the dialog width.                      │      │   │
│  │  └──────┘   └───────────────────────────────────────┘      │   │
│  │                                                              │   │
│  │  [Options - if present]                                      │   │
│  │  > Option 1 (selected)                                      │   │
│  │    Option 2                                                 │   │
│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│                                                                    │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

